# Blog - GitHub repository URL for fetching blog posts
# Format: owner/repo (e.g. vetrecord/blog-posts) or https://github.com/owner/repo
# Create a repo with a "posts" folder containing .md/.mdx files with frontmatter:
#
# ---
# title: My Post Title
# description: SEO description for the post
# date: 2025-01-15
# image: hero.jpg
# author: Author Name
# ---
#
# Your markdown content with ![images](./image.png)...
BLOG_GITHUB_REPO_URL=dragoslavIvkovic/blogpost

# Optional: GitHub branch (default: main)
BLOG_GITHUB_BRANCH=main

# Optional: Path to posts folder in repo (default: posts)
BLOG_GITHUB_POSTS_PATH=posts

# Optional: GitHub token for higher API rate limits (recommended for production)
# BLOG_GITHUB_TOKEN=
